.START 

NCNB Corp., Charlotte, N.C., said it plans to offer five million new shares of common, exclusively in the Japanese market, at $51 a share. 

The bank holding company said the Nomura Securities Co. is the managing underwriter for the sale. 

Proceeds from the stock sale, which will be used for general corporate purposes, are about $250 million.
NCNB previously made a public offering in Japan in mid-1987. 

NCNB shares closed yesterday at $51.375, up 37.5 cents, in New York Stock Exchange composite trading. 

